snippet: The Muslim Brotherhood teamed up with other Islamists to establish a new political party that is likely to be a leading player in the the country’s first elections since the overthrow of Col. Muammar el-Qaddafi.
abstract: Libya's Muslim Brotherhood teams up with other Islamists to establish a new political party that is likely to be leading player in country's first elections since the overthrow of Col Muammar el-Qaddafi; Libyans will vote in June for a national assembly that will draft a new constitution.
lead_paragraph: The Muslim Brotherhood teamed up with other Islamists to establish a new political party that is likely to be a leading player in the the country’s first elections since the overthrow of Col. Muammar el-Qaddafi.
